A 19-year-old has appeared in court in connection with the gruesome murder of Welkom student, Naledi Lethoba. WELKOM - The family of Naledi Lethoba are left in pain and with so many unanswered questions following their daughter's death. The 21-year-old's body was found burnt and mutilated in an open field last month. Lethoba was laid to rest on Saturday, as her parents seek justice. READ: Gruesome details of Klarinet child murders emerge A 19-year-old has since appeared in court in connection with the gruesome murder of the Welkom student. The murder accused is a fellow student at Goldfields TVET College. The motive for the murder is unknown and the suspect is expected to appear in court on 14 June for a formal bail application.